<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="13" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="14.[192,1440,1434,1621]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,364,1434,1458]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Life history.</emphasis>
Larvae have been recorded feeding on the leaves of five species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Schreb." authorityName="Schreb." box="[1225,1440,1434,1458]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Vernonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1225,1337,1435,1458]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Vernonia</emphasis>
Schreb.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[200,336,1467,1491]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
) in the 
<collectingCountry box="[433,491,1467,1491]" name="United States of America" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">USA</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Matthews, D. L. &amp; T. A. Lott" box="[507,815,1467,1491]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" pagination="1 - 324" refId="ref20718" refString="Matthews, D. L., and T. A. Lott 2005. Larval hostplants of the Pterophoridae (Lepidoptera: Pterophoroidea). Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute 76: 1 - 324. ISBN: 1 - 887988 - 20 - 3." type="journal article" year="2005">Matthews and Lott 2005</bibRefCitation>
). Although larval specimens have not yet been collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[308,483,1499,1523]" name="Bahamas" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">The Bahamas</collectingCountry>
, adults were found in association with 
<taxonomicName authority="Small" authorityName="Small" authorityYear="1903" box="[978,1297,1499,1523]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Vernonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="blodgettii">
<emphasis box="[978,1215,1499,1523]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Vernonia blodgettii</emphasis>
Small
</taxonomicName>
growing in recently burned pinelands. These adults were found flying in close proximity to the plants, perching on the plants, and in two cases, nectaring on the flowers. Three other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1169,1281,1565,1588]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Vernonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1169,1281,1565,1588]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Vernonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occur in 
<collectingCountry name="Bahamas" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">The Bahamas</collectingCountry>
, two endemic and one widespread in the tropics and subtropics (
<bibRefCitation author="Correll, D. S. &amp; H. B. Correll" box="[1098,1401,1597,1621]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" refId="ref20417" refString="Correll, D. S., and H. B. Correll. 1982. Flora of the Bahama Archipelago (Including the Turks and Caicos Islands). Gantner Verlag; Vaduz, Liechtenstein. 1692 p." type="book" year="1982">Correll and Correll 1982</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="13" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="14.[192,1440,1645,1734]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,371,1645,1669]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Distribution.</emphasis>
This species is widespread across the 
<collectingCountry box="[834,892,1645,1669]" name="United States of America" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">USA</collectingCountry>
and ranges north into 
<collectingCountry box="[1170,1268,1645,1669]" name="Canada" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Canada</collectingCountry>
. In 
<collectingCountry name="Bahamas" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">The Bahamas</collectingCountry>
it has only been collected on North and 
<collectingRegion box="[745,904,1678,1702]" country="Bahamas" name="South Abaco" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">South Abaco</collectingRegion>
. In the neotropics it has also been reported in 
<collectingCountry box="[224,367,1710,1734]" name="Puerto Rico" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Puerto Rico</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Moschler, H. B." box="[382,572,1710,1734]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" pagination="69 - 360" refId="ref21159" refString="Moschler, H. B. 1890. Die Lepidopteren-Fauna der Insel Porto Rico. Abhandlungen Herausgegeben von der Senckenbergischen Naturforschenden Gesellschaft 16: 69 - 360." type="journal article" year="1890">Möschler, 1890</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
